<br>
Yup, I got the belt, once.  ONCE was all it took.  Never wanted that to happen again.<br>
<br>
I got smacked a couple of times for being mouthy, mostly in my teenage years.  I learned not to get mouthy.  <br>
<br>
I've got nothing but respect for my mother.  I'm not screaming about how abused I was, or how messed up in the head I am cuz I got a belt to my backside.<br>
<br>
Nowadays parents aren't allowed to do even that without worrying about what the neighbors will do, and people wonder why we have such disrespectful little bastards running around?  Puh-lease.  I guarentee if half those kids had been spanked when they'd done wrong, they'd have a bit more respect for everyone around them.<br>
<br>
Case in point, my cousin's children.  Three of the biggest brats I have ever seen.  Mouthy little shits, with no respect for their mother.  In fact they'll often tell her &quot;You can't hit me cuz I'll tell on you&quot;, so she doesn't.  The only person in the family who can make them behave, say in a restuarant?  My mother.  Cuz they know she'll smack their lil behinds til they're a nice rosy red.  If she's around, they're on their best behaviour.  Too bad for my cousin that we live 1000 miles away now.<br>
<br>
My point?  Discipline for children is not a bad thing.  Flat-out abuse is.  But there *IS* a difference.  Too bad people are too worried about being PC these days to figure that out.<br>
